This paper discusses encrypted databases and their vulnerabilities, which falls under the category of database security (cs.DB) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of trusted computing platforms, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations and improvements of encrypted databases, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CY).
